WEBVTT

00:03.071 --> 00:04.505
Okay, Connie.
We've talked enough.

00:04.538 --> 00:06.240
[ Telephone beeps ]

00:06.274 --> 00:07.075
Why are you making
that face?

00:07.108 --> 00:08.242
What are you reading?

00:08.276 --> 00:10.378
My mom's homework for
her English class.

00:10.411 --> 00:11.979
Listen to what she put down
for the answers --

00:12.012 --> 00:14.715
"The loaf of bread is...
sad."

00:14.748 --> 00:17.185
"The puppy is...
broken."

00:17.218 --> 00:19.920
"The seashells are...
all dead."

00:19.953 --> 00:21.489
I know, she's a terrible
student.

00:21.522 --> 00:22.756
I think she's lonely.

00:22.790 --> 00:24.558
It's tough being her age
at this time of the year.

00:24.592 --> 00:25.859
Statistically.

00:25.893 --> 00:27.061
The holiday blues.

00:27.095 --> 00:28.696
Louis,
I know your mother.

00:28.729 --> 00:30.198
She's not lonely.

00:30.231 --> 00:33.401
Her English isn't good
because she never practices.

00:33.434 --> 00:35.035
Except when she swears
at the mailman

00:35.069 --> 00:36.104
because her coupons
are late.

00:36.137 --> 00:37.171
[Bleep] [Bleep]

00:37.205 --> 00:38.872
[Bleep] [Bleep] [Bleep]

00:38.906 --> 00:41.842
[Bleep]
Twice!

00:41.875 --> 00:44.078
I'll say this, her English
is great when she swears.

00:44.112 --> 00:45.179
It's a different part
of her brain.

00:45.213 --> 00:46.380
So, I just told
my sister

00:46.414 --> 00:48.282
we're not going to her house
for Thanksgiving

00:48.316 --> 00:50.118
because we're opening
the restaurant again this year.

00:50.151 --> 00:51.785
Mm.

00:51.819 --> 00:54.755
I wish we could just jump
to the day after Thanksgiving.

00:54.788 --> 00:56.757
Black Friday.

00:56.790 --> 00:58.359
No relatives.

00:58.392 --> 01:00.228
Christmas songs
come on the radio.

01:00.261 --> 01:02.130
Tupperware bulging
with leftovers.

01:02.163 --> 01:04.898
Me and Honey finally
outsmarting the shopping lines.

01:04.932 --> 01:06.300
We'll use your mother's
wheelchair

01:06.334 --> 01:08.102
and cut straight
to the front.

01:08.136 --> 01:10.571
I'm gonna take a bed nap
and a couch nap that day.

01:10.604 --> 01:13.774
I am going to get us
a brand-new fridge for so cheap.

01:13.807 --> 01:16.277
[ Sighing ] The day
after Thanksgiving.

01:16.310 --> 01:17.411
[ Sighs ]

01:17.445 --> 01:19.113
There's nothing better.

01:19.147 --> 01:21.282
This is a nightmare!
I hope you're happy!

01:21.315 --> 01:22.983
Me?!
This is all your fault!

01:23.016 --> 01:24.051
Look what you
did to him!

01:24.084 --> 01:25.619
This is on you!
You did this!

01:25.653 --> 01:28.956
[ Hauntingly ]
* I love you, you love me

01:28.989 --> 01:32.260
* we're a happy family

01:32.293 --> 01:33.661
Why would you say
it's my fault?!
Because it's your --

01:33.694 --> 01:34.662
[ Dish clatters ]

01:34.695 --> 01:37.165
Go screw.

01:37.198 --> 01:38.332
At least I wasn't doing it
for selfish reasons.
It's always "Eddie,
Eddie, Eddie!"

01:38.366 --> 01:39.500
When is it ever
your fault?!
You pressured it --

01:39.533 --> 01:42.002
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:42.035 --> 01:43.237
* Fresh off the boat

01:43.271 --> 01:44.838
* I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go *

01:44.872 --> 01:46.974
* If you don't know, homey,
now you know *

01:47.007 --> 01:48.509
* Fresh off the boat

01:48.542 --> 01:50.678
* Homey, you don't know
where I come from *

01:50.711 --> 01:52.012
* But I know where I'm goin'

01:52.045 --> 01:54.047
* I'm fresh off the boat

01:57.718 --> 02:00.554
**

02:05.159 --> 02:06.294
It's not my fault.

02:06.327 --> 02:08.596
Your nails have ridges
like potato chips.

02:08.629 --> 02:10.030
Grandma?

02:10.063 --> 02:11.165
I know a movie
you should do

02:11.199 --> 02:12.666
for your ESL final
monologue --

02:12.700 --> 02:13.801
"The Sandlot."

02:18.138 --> 02:20.308
Mom, can you take me to
the Teacher Supply Store?

02:20.341 --> 02:21.809
I need a 3-hole punch,

02:21.842 --> 02:23.277
one with some cojones.

02:23.311 --> 02:24.278
I can't. I'm busy.

02:24.312 --> 02:25.846
Fine. I'll walk.

02:25.879 --> 02:27.615
Not by yourself,
you won't.

02:27.648 --> 02:28.816
Why not?

02:28.849 --> 02:30.451
I'm in middle school now.
Just like Emery.

02:30.484 --> 02:31.819
It's different.
Emery's older.

02:31.852 --> 02:33.020
You skipped a grade.

02:33.053 --> 02:34.722
Because I'm so mature.

02:34.755 --> 02:37.558
You just had me buy you
a Barney the Dinosaur lamp.

02:37.591 --> 02:40.060
A plain lamp or a lamp
with an icon on it

02:40.093 --> 02:42.129
for the same price.

02:42.162 --> 02:43.997
[ Scoffs ] I mean,
really, where am I?

02:44.031 --> 02:45.866
Ask one of your brothers
if they'll take you.

02:45.899 --> 02:47.468
Otherwise, you can't go.

02:47.501 --> 02:49.169
[ Sighs ]
Cut the cord already.

02:51.772 --> 02:54.174
[ Door opens and closes ]

02:54.208 --> 02:56.810
"One Crazy Summer." Joel Murray.
Any line. They're all brilliant.

02:56.844 --> 02:57.978
Bill Murray's brother?

02:58.011 --> 02:59.847
Brian Doyle-Murray's brother?

02:59.880 --> 03:01.048
There's three of them?

03:01.081 --> 03:02.583
Ugh, my God.

03:02.616 --> 03:04.518
Dinner at the Murrays'
must have been exhausting.

03:04.552 --> 03:07.255
Everybody trying so hard
while pretending not to.

03:07.288 --> 03:08.422
I got some bad news.

03:08.456 --> 03:09.757
Matthew Chestnut said we can't

03:09.790 --> 03:12.593
open the restaurant
on Thanksgiving.
Why not?

03:12.626 --> 03:15.329
Apparently the holiday's
sacred to Kenny Rogers.

03:15.363 --> 03:17.431
Something about being
part Native American,

03:17.465 --> 03:20.067
and how he lost his
virginity on that day.
Folksy.

03:20.100 --> 03:20.934
Yeah, well, there
goes our excuse

03:20.968 --> 03:22.202
to get out of Thanksgiving.

03:22.236 --> 03:23.203
What do we do now?

03:23.237 --> 03:24.838
Well, my family's
in D.C.

03:24.872 --> 03:27.040
They won't know if
we worked or not.

03:27.074 --> 03:28.075
Yeah...

03:31.211 --> 03:33.514
I'll smash the cordless and
siphon the gas from the car,

03:33.547 --> 03:35.115
say we're victims of
a holiday crime wave --

03:35.148 --> 03:36.417
couldn't call even
if we wanted.

03:36.450 --> 03:37.918
Or we just don't
say anything

03:37.951 --> 03:39.453
and they'll assume
we worked.

03:39.487 --> 03:41.021
Yeah.
That's a good plan, too.

03:41.054 --> 03:43.190
Now we don't have to
suffer work or family,

03:43.223 --> 03:45.793
and I can focus on
Black Friday.

03:45.826 --> 03:47.295
Me and Honey
are deciding

03:47.328 --> 03:49.330
who's gonna push the other
in the wheelchair.

03:52.666 --> 03:53.767
What? Why?

04:00.274 --> 04:01.675
[ Sighs ]

04:09.517 --> 04:10.818
Hmm?

04:10.851 --> 04:11.985
[ Coins clattering ]

04:12.019 --> 04:13.120
Hey.

04:13.153 --> 04:14.254
I need you guys
to take me

04:14.288 --> 04:15.623
to the Teacher
Supply Store.

04:15.656 --> 04:16.624
Forget it.

04:16.657 --> 04:17.791
We're going to
the mall.

04:17.825 --> 04:18.992
You're welcome
to come.

04:19.026 --> 04:20.428
It's my first
Thanksgiving since

04:20.461 --> 04:21.729
Alison and I broke up.

04:21.762 --> 04:23.664
I can't risk the blues.

04:23.697 --> 04:26.066
This time of the year is the
toughest on single teenagers.

04:26.099 --> 04:27.601
Statistically.

04:27.635 --> 04:29.403
He said he heard it
on "Povich."

04:29.437 --> 04:30.938
Maury does his research.

04:30.971 --> 04:32.440
I need a distraction,

04:32.473 --> 04:34.107
so we're gonna hit up
the holiday ice rink.

04:34.141 --> 04:35.643
It's always a sea of girls.

04:35.676 --> 04:37.345
They don't open the rink
until Friday,

04:37.378 --> 04:39.447
so you can take me
to the supply store now.

04:39.480 --> 04:41.682
No. We're going to the mall
to shop for socks.

04:41.715 --> 04:43.851
Who buys socks a month out
from Christmas?

04:43.884 --> 04:45.586
Socks are Santa's job.

04:45.619 --> 04:47.020
I need pimp socks.

04:47.054 --> 04:49.122
The skate changing area
is co-ed.

04:49.156 --> 04:52.025
I can't walk around
in these...chump things.

04:53.461 --> 04:55.195
You need to cut
your toenails.

04:57.665 --> 04:59.767
I'm talking about taking
your body to heaven

04:59.800 --> 05:01.769
and sending your mind south.

05:01.802 --> 05:04.304
I'm talking about
spoiling you so bad

05:04.338 --> 05:06.306
you'll hate every other
woman you touch.

05:06.340 --> 05:08.842
I'm talking about
my mouth on your mouth,

05:08.876 --> 05:10.811
and my tongue
anywhere you --

05:10.844 --> 05:12.145
All right, cut.

05:12.179 --> 05:13.681
[ Applause ]

05:13.714 --> 05:16.850
Let's hear it for Donnie...

05:16.884 --> 05:20.153
channeling his inner Streisand.

05:20.187 --> 05:25.626
And now, for our final act of
ESL's Night-Out-At-The-Movies,

05:25.659 --> 05:30.831
we have Jenny Huang reciting
from Tim Burton's "Batman."

05:30.864 --> 05:33.567
[ Light applause ]

05:33.601 --> 05:36.637
Looks live I saved
the best for last.

05:36.670 --> 05:38.372
Professor.

05:38.406 --> 05:41.542
Gotham is a lucky city
tonight.

05:44.578 --> 05:46.647
[ Clears throat ]

05:46.680 --> 05:51.385
Let me tell you about
this guy I know, Jack.

05:53.220 --> 05:55.423
I've never seen
so many socks.

05:55.456 --> 05:57.691
They had a whole section
devoted to frogs!

05:57.725 --> 05:59.259
The mall --
it's got everything.

05:59.292 --> 06:02.329
Except a 3-hole punch
worth a damn.

06:02.362 --> 06:04.231
Hey, want to see
that movie?

06:04.264 --> 06:05.599
"I Know What You Did
Last Summer"?

06:05.633 --> 06:07.034
It's rated R.

06:07.067 --> 06:08.936
Walter works at the theater.
He'll let us in.

06:08.969 --> 06:11.171
Evan's too young to see
an R-rated movie.

06:11.204 --> 06:13.441
I saw my first R
when I was 7.

06:13.474 --> 06:15.443
"The Fabulous
Baker Boys."

06:15.476 --> 06:17.177
Evan's not like you.

06:17.210 --> 06:19.112
Yeah, he skips grades,

06:19.146 --> 06:21.949
shops at teacher stores,
and he uses napkins.

06:21.982 --> 06:23.517
He's way more mature
than I was.

06:23.551 --> 06:26.754
He's book smart,
not street smart.
Exactly.

06:26.787 --> 06:28.856
And it's our job as older
brothers to toughen him up.

06:28.889 --> 06:30.624
I don't know.

06:30.658 --> 06:32.460
Evan.

06:32.493 --> 06:34.027
Would you like to
go see "Flubber"

06:34.061 --> 06:35.696
or "I Know What You Did
Last Summer"?

06:35.729 --> 06:38.699
Both have really
strong casts.

06:38.732 --> 06:40.768
Mom would want you to see the
little kids' movie "Flubber."

06:40.801 --> 06:41.969
You should definitely
go see that.

06:42.002 --> 06:43.270
I'm not a little kid.

06:43.303 --> 06:44.972
I'm a pre-tween.

06:45.005 --> 06:47.441
"Flubber" can go
flub itself.

06:47.475 --> 06:49.076
Yes!

06:51.278 --> 06:54.147
Hey, great job
up there, Mom.

06:54.181 --> 06:55.583
I mean, Bruce Wayne.

06:55.616 --> 06:56.584
[ As Michael Keaton ]
"Now you wanna get nuts?

06:56.617 --> 06:57.751
C'mon, let's get nuts."

06:57.785 --> 06:59.753
Mom?

06:59.787 --> 07:02.456
Jenny, you told me you
didn't have any kids.

07:02.490 --> 07:03.423
She did?

07:03.457 --> 07:05.425
You did?

07:05.459 --> 07:07.761
[ Laughs heartily ]

07:07.795 --> 07:09.329
[ Chuckling ]

07:09.362 --> 07:10.330
You got me!

07:10.363 --> 07:11.799
You must be Louis.

07:11.832 --> 07:13.166
Bernard.

07:13.200 --> 07:15.168
I've heard a lot
about you.

07:15.202 --> 07:16.470
Well, it's nice
to meet you.

07:16.504 --> 07:18.672
My mom can't say enough
about your class.

07:18.706 --> 07:21.274
And you.
Well, the pleasure
was all mine.

07:21.308 --> 07:22.576
A model student.

07:22.610 --> 07:25.178
I can't believe
it's almost over.

07:25.212 --> 07:27.581
I'm gonna miss her.
Miss her?

07:27.615 --> 07:29.182
Only a final exam left,

07:29.216 --> 07:31.752
and then she'll flap
out of my life.

07:31.785 --> 07:33.186
Like the Batman.

07:33.220 --> 07:35.923
[ Laughs heartily ]

07:35.956 --> 07:39.026
**

07:39.059 --> 07:41.361
I invited Bernard
to Thanksgiving!

07:47.067 --> 07:48.301
So now I have
to race around

07:48.335 --> 07:49.970
and whip up
a Thanksgiving dinner

07:50.003 --> 07:52.706
because you invited
your mother's teacher?

07:52.740 --> 07:55.509
Jessica, I have never seen
my mom this happy ever.

07:55.543 --> 07:57.044
Bernard is the answer
to her loneliness.

07:57.077 --> 07:59.212
Come on, Louis,
wake up!

07:59.246 --> 08:01.448
She's just trying
to work him for an "A."

08:01.481 --> 08:03.150
But the goal is
to improve her English.

08:03.183 --> 08:04.117
Why would she care
about her grade?

08:04.151 --> 08:05.686
Because she's a human.

08:05.719 --> 08:07.320
Everybody wants an "A."

08:07.354 --> 08:09.222
No, you should have seen them.
The connection was obvious.

08:09.256 --> 08:10.558
You could tell
he was interested,

08:10.591 --> 08:12.192
but he's clearly
an honorable man.

08:12.225 --> 08:14.161
He didn't want to cross
the teacher-student line.

08:14.194 --> 08:17.064
Like Amy Fisher,
the Long Island Lolita.

08:17.097 --> 08:19.567
No, that's way off.
Buttafuoco was her mechanic.

08:19.600 --> 08:21.168
The point is,
they both need a chance

08:21.201 --> 08:22.836
to get to know each other
outside of class.

08:22.870 --> 08:24.538
So take them
on a boat ride!

08:24.572 --> 08:25.573
I am not going --

08:25.606 --> 08:27.374
Jessica!

08:39.620 --> 08:41.221
Hmm?

08:44.257 --> 08:46.660
But you've never offered
to pay for anything.

08:46.694 --> 08:47.761
Ever.

08:50.598 --> 08:51.965
Mm, no, you didn't.

08:55.135 --> 08:56.570
Clean cotton.

09:00.941 --> 09:02.509
[ Laughter on television ]

09:02.542 --> 09:03.677
Have you talked
to Evan?

09:03.711 --> 09:04.845
"I Know What You Did
Last Summer"

09:04.878 --> 09:06.046
really messed him up.

09:06.079 --> 09:07.748
He had nightmares
all night.

09:07.781 --> 09:09.516
It's a horror movie.

09:09.549 --> 09:10.718
It's supposed to
scare you.

09:10.751 --> 09:12.419
What if the stress
gets to be too much

09:12.452 --> 09:13.887
and he cries to Mom,

09:13.921 --> 09:15.856
says that we took him to
an R-rated movie?

09:15.889 --> 09:17.557
Bye-bye, ice skating.

09:17.591 --> 09:19.426
Bye-bye, gentleman socks.
Pimp socks.

09:19.459 --> 09:22.062
Pimping is not all goblets
and dancing.

09:22.095 --> 09:23.931
It's women suffering,
Eddie.

09:27.000 --> 09:28.602
We need to talk to him.

09:28.636 --> 09:30.137
Make sure he's okay.

09:30.170 --> 09:31.905
Help him through it.

09:31.939 --> 09:33.641
Hey, Evan, want
to go ride bikes?

09:33.674 --> 09:35.108
So we can accidentally hit
a fisherman

09:35.142 --> 09:36.610
and pay for it
with our lives?

09:36.644 --> 09:37.911
No, thanks.

09:37.945 --> 09:40.814
And if you were smart,
you wouldn't go either.

09:40.848 --> 09:44.184
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

09:46.453 --> 09:49.589
**

09:49.623 --> 09:50.758
Knock knock!

09:50.791 --> 09:52.292
Happy Thanksgiving!

09:52.325 --> 09:54.461
Oh, you mean,
Happy Drinks-giving.
[ Both chuckle ]

09:54.494 --> 09:56.930
This is one of my top-five
drinking holidays.

09:56.964 --> 09:58.431
I am going all-out.

09:58.465 --> 10:01.001
It could be the last one I get
to enjoy before I'm pregnant.

10:01.034 --> 10:03.436
Yeah, could be.

10:03.470 --> 10:04.738
Well, if you make it
past noon,

10:04.772 --> 10:06.573
you're welcome to
come over to my house.

10:06.606 --> 10:08.842
Well, thanks, but we
already made plans.

10:08.876 --> 10:10.678
I thought you guys weren't
having Thanksgiving this year.

10:10.711 --> 10:13.613
Well, Louis invited his mother's
ESL teacher over,

10:13.647 --> 10:16.083
so she's cooking the whole meal
by herself.

10:16.116 --> 10:17.250
She is?

10:17.284 --> 10:18.819
But she'll miss
the Macy's Parade.

10:18.852 --> 10:20.788
VCR'ing it.
Oh, damn.

10:20.821 --> 10:22.489
It's like she's a whole
other person --

10:22.522 --> 10:25.092
courteous, polite, kind.

10:25.125 --> 10:27.427
Just the type of person
we can convince

10:27.460 --> 10:29.930
into letting us borrow
her wheelchair.

10:29.963 --> 10:31.598
I'll drink a shot
to that.

10:31.631 --> 10:32.632
You too, Emily.

10:32.666 --> 10:34.167
Keep pace.

10:37.905 --> 10:40.007
Boys!

10:40.040 --> 10:43.210
Okay, everyone on
their best behavior.

10:43.243 --> 10:44.644
This is important
to Grandma.

10:44.678 --> 10:47.014
Is someone gonna search him
for a knife?
What?

10:47.047 --> 10:48.348
He's kidding.
Making a joke.

10:48.381 --> 10:49.349
No jokes.
[ Doorbell rings ]

10:49.382 --> 10:50.183
Grandma: Oh!

10:54.221 --> 10:55.689
Hello, teacher!

10:55.723 --> 10:58.726
Gobble, gobble.
As the turkey says.

10:58.759 --> 11:01.394
Happy Thanksgiving, Jenny.

11:01.428 --> 11:03.363
Louis. Boys.

11:03.396 --> 11:04.631
Hello, Jessica.

11:04.664 --> 11:05.966
Hello, Bernard.
Welcome.

11:05.999 --> 11:07.500
Happy Thanksgiving.

11:07.534 --> 11:10.370
I brought a chilled bottle
of Sauvignon Blanc

11:10.403 --> 11:13.140
and Jenny's last
homework assignment...

11:13.173 --> 11:14.307
an "A."

11:14.341 --> 11:16.243
"A."

11:16.276 --> 11:19.412
Uh, well, one for inside
the fridge. One for outside.

11:19.446 --> 11:21.214
[ Laughs heartily ]

11:21.248 --> 11:22.415
Yes! Yes!

11:22.449 --> 11:23.516
Amazing!

11:23.550 --> 11:24.818
Let's eat!

11:24.852 --> 11:26.586
Teacher on vacay!

11:26.619 --> 11:28.021
Okay, well,
come inside.

11:28.055 --> 11:34.427
**

11:34.461 --> 11:37.831
Yum, yum, yum, yum, yum.

11:37.865 --> 11:41.001
Yum, yum, yum, yum, yum,
yum, yum.

11:41.034 --> 11:43.003
Yum, yum, yum, yum.

11:43.036 --> 11:44.071
Ore-gone.

11:44.104 --> 11:45.372
Orr-eh-gan.

11:45.405 --> 11:46.406
Ore-gone.

11:46.439 --> 11:48.008
Orr-eh-gan.

11:48.041 --> 11:49.276
Mrs. Dash, huh?

11:50.744 --> 11:52.512
Where's Mr. Dash?

11:52.545 --> 11:54.447
[ Laughs heartily ]

11:54.481 --> 11:56.449
You see, Oliver...

11:56.483 --> 11:59.452
in this life,
one thing counts.

11:59.486 --> 12:02.555
In the bank, large amounts.

12:02.589 --> 12:05.392
* I'm afraid these
don't grow on trees *

12:05.425 --> 12:07.928
* You've got to pick
a pocket or two *

12:07.961 --> 12:11.431
* You've got to pick
a pocket or two, boys *

12:11.464 --> 12:13.433
[ Falsetto ] * Large amounts
don't grow on trees *

12:13.466 --> 12:15.735
* You've got to pick
a pocket or two *

12:15.769 --> 12:17.404
[ Laughs heartily ]

12:17.437 --> 12:19.439
[ Laughs heartily ]

12:19.472 --> 12:24.912
[ Laughs heartily ]

12:24.945 --> 12:27.447
[ Burps ]

12:27.480 --> 12:28.782
[ Fork clinks ]

12:28.816 --> 12:31.384
[ Television chatter ]

12:31.418 --> 12:33.486
Grandma's new boyfriend.

12:33.520 --> 12:34.621
Oof.

12:36.356 --> 12:38.658
Hey, Evan...

12:38.691 --> 12:39.893
want to watch
the parade with us?

12:39.927 --> 12:41.094
Grandma taped it.

12:41.128 --> 12:43.163
No, thanks.
Come on.

12:43.196 --> 12:45.598
Some nice family friendly
entertainment never hurt anyone.

12:47.700 --> 12:49.436
Hey, there's
the Rugrats!

12:49.469 --> 12:51.238
And Sonic the Hedgehog!

12:51.271 --> 12:53.306
See? No scary
bad guys here.

12:53.340 --> 12:54.774
Just like real life.

12:54.808 --> 12:56.243
Yep.
It's all good.

12:56.276 --> 12:58.078
No need to tell Mom
anything, right?

12:58.111 --> 12:59.813
Shh!
I'm trying to watch.

12:59.847 --> 13:01.314
Barney's up next!

13:03.884 --> 13:05.752
Man: Oh, there's another gust.

13:05.785 --> 13:07.254
It's so windy.

13:07.287 --> 13:09.089
They better hold on.

13:09.122 --> 13:11.758
[ Crowd screaming ]

13:11.791 --> 13:14.461
Oh no, Barney!

13:14.494 --> 13:16.696
Oh, he's been gutted!

13:16.729 --> 13:19.366
And it looks like the cops
are going in with knives

13:19.399 --> 13:20.868
to slice up the rest of him.

13:20.901 --> 13:24.938
[ Screaming ]

13:24.972 --> 13:27.875
Well, pie time.

13:27.908 --> 13:30.510
You done with that?
Um, I --

13:30.543 --> 13:34.714
Can't let your mom's good work
go to waste, right, son?

13:34.747 --> 13:37.250
Yum, yum.
Mmm!

13:38.185 --> 13:40.187
You know, I was just
thinking how much better

13:40.220 --> 13:43.123
your homework would look
on a brand-new fridge.

13:43.156 --> 13:44.524
I hope there's
one still left

13:44.557 --> 13:46.826
by the time I get to the front
of the line tomorrow.

13:49.396 --> 13:50.363
Oh.

13:50.397 --> 13:52.032
Oh, I couldn't.

13:52.065 --> 13:53.500
I know you're not
comfortable with it.

13:59.907 --> 14:02.409
Jessica,
can I speak with you a moment?

14:02.442 --> 14:06.179
Bernard: May I speak with you
a moment.

14:06.213 --> 14:08.481
I can't take it anymore.
We have to get rid of him.

14:08.515 --> 14:11.251
Oh, come on,
he's not that bad.
Not that bad?

14:11.284 --> 14:12.185
[ As Bernard ]
Yum, yum, yum.

14:12.219 --> 14:14.021
Yum, yum, yum, yum, yum.
Yum, yum.

14:14.054 --> 14:16.156
Yum, yum, yum,
yum, yum.
Okay, what about
your mother's happiness?

14:16.189 --> 14:17.590
I thought you said
she was lonely.

14:17.624 --> 14:18.758
[ Normal voice ]
Well, I was all for it

14:18.791 --> 14:20.027
until I realized it
might be permanent.

14:20.060 --> 14:21.694
He called me his son.

14:21.728 --> 14:24.231
Can you imagine dealing
with that clown every day?

14:24.264 --> 14:26.166
Do you hear how
selfish you sound?

14:26.199 --> 14:27.400
Who are you kidding?

14:27.434 --> 14:28.668
You're only putting up
with him

14:28.701 --> 14:30.103
so you could use
her wheelchair

14:30.137 --> 14:31.371
to jump
the Black Friday line.

14:31.404 --> 14:33.273
Okay, fine!

14:33.306 --> 14:35.508
I admit that, and I'm
not gonna let you blow it

14:35.542 --> 14:38.611
just 'cause you can't
handle a little...

14:38.645 --> 14:40.347
energy.

14:40.380 --> 14:41.949
[ As Bernard ] A-yum yum yum yum
yum yum yum yum yum yum --

14:41.982 --> 14:44.284
Stop it!
Okay. Okay.

14:44.317 --> 14:46.553
We just have to suck it up
for a few more hours.

14:46.586 --> 14:49.756
Then I get my chair,
and your mother stays happy.

14:49.789 --> 14:51.558
[ Normal voice ]
You're right. You're right.

14:51.591 --> 14:53.626
Besides,
she's gonna be over him

14:53.660 --> 14:55.228
as soon as she gets
an "A" in that class.

14:55.262 --> 14:57.530
I told you, the grade
doesn't matter.

14:57.564 --> 14:59.899
Their diploma is a button
that says "Hooray!"

15:04.404 --> 15:05.973
Where's Bernard?

15:06.006 --> 15:07.975
Too much.

15:08.008 --> 15:09.742
Broke up.

15:09.776 --> 15:12.479
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, thank the lord!

15:12.512 --> 15:13.947
I'm sorry, Mom,
but you're better off.

15:13.981 --> 15:15.215
He was the worst.

15:15.248 --> 15:16.749
It's like,
read the room, pal.

15:16.783 --> 15:18.218
You're annoying as hell.

15:18.251 --> 15:19.652
Okay, Louis,
that's enough.

15:19.686 --> 15:21.488
You think three
Murray brothers is a lot?

15:21.521 --> 15:23.323
He was like 50 Murray brothers
rolled into one,

15:23.356 --> 15:24.757
with five Martin Shorts.

15:24.791 --> 15:26.293
Mom, you could do
so much better.

15:26.326 --> 15:28.761
Bernard:
I believe she meant to say

15:28.795 --> 15:32.265
I "ate too much,"
and that I "threw up."

15:36.203 --> 15:40.140
I give this family...
an "F."

15:41.874 --> 15:44.144
Sorry about
your bathroom.

15:46.313 --> 15:49.116
[ Door opens, closes ]

15:49.149 --> 15:50.483
Louis, how could you?
[ Telephone ringing ]

15:50.517 --> 15:53.253
Don't you care about
your mother at all?

15:53.286 --> 15:56.523
Or is it just Louis, Louis,
Louis all the time?

15:56.556 --> 15:58.191
[ Answering machine beeps ]

15:58.225 --> 16:00.093
Honey: [ Slurred ]
Hey, Jess-nuts!

16:00.127 --> 16:02.996
Just checkin' in to see if you
tricked Ol' Wheely Wheels

16:03.030 --> 16:06.466
to lend you her steel so we
can cut asses in line maÃ±ana,

16:06.499 --> 16:08.435
get you that new fridge!

16:08.468 --> 16:10.137
Let a bitch know, bitch!
Whoooo--
[ Answering machine beeps ]

16:14.474 --> 16:16.776
[ Macy's Parade chatter
on television ]

16:16.809 --> 16:18.611
Man: Oh, there's another gust.

16:18.645 --> 16:21.881
Hey, Ma. We heated up some of
the delicious turkey you made.

16:21.914 --> 16:23.083
Want us to make you
a plate?

16:27.987 --> 16:29.756
She's still
mad at us.
Yep. Yep.

16:32.659 --> 16:34.427
Oh, Grandma,
don't watch this part!

16:38.098 --> 16:39.366
Why would you do that?

16:51.044 --> 16:53.380
Hmm.
I'm always the balloon.

16:53.413 --> 16:55.382
Eddie and Emery tricked me
into seeing a scary movie.

17:00.753 --> 17:02.255
Is that from "Batman"?

17:08.795 --> 17:11.398
Even leftovers
don't taste good.

17:11.431 --> 17:13.566
Well, just put them
in that dull, tiny fridge

17:13.600 --> 17:16.403
with no crisper that we're
stuck with until next year.

17:16.436 --> 17:18.905
None of this would have happened
if my mom had learned her verbs.

17:18.938 --> 17:21.208
I don't blame her, anyway.
I blame Honey.

17:21.241 --> 17:22.675
That drunk.

17:22.709 --> 17:25.212
Sad. Drinking that much
on Thanksgiving.

17:25.245 --> 17:26.546
[ Bottle clatters ]

17:26.579 --> 17:28.248
[ Snoring ]

17:28.281 --> 17:30.583
One of us should apologize
to my mom.

17:30.617 --> 17:32.119
Yeah.

17:32.152 --> 17:34.554
And it should be the person
who is really at fault --

17:34.587 --> 17:35.655
you.

17:38.391 --> 17:39.892
What are you doing?
Holding up a mirror.

17:39.926 --> 17:41.428
Do you see yourself?

17:41.461 --> 17:42.962
You took advantage of
a woman's happiness

17:42.995 --> 17:44.297
so you could use
her wheelchair.

17:44.331 --> 17:45.565
Well, what about you?

17:45.598 --> 17:47.634
Every second with
the love connections,

17:47.667 --> 17:51.138
always trying to be that chubby
baby fatso with the wings.

17:51.171 --> 17:53.039
Cupid.
If you hadn't meddled,

17:53.072 --> 17:54.574
we wouldn't have hosted
Thanksgiving

17:54.607 --> 17:56.276
and everything
would be fine!

17:56.309 --> 17:58.545
At least I wasn't doing it for
selfish reasons like you.

17:58.578 --> 17:59.779
I was trying to be nice.

17:59.812 --> 18:01.714
My mom was lonely,
and I wanted to help her.

18:01.748 --> 18:03.883
No one is lonely, Louis.

18:03.916 --> 18:05.718
That's not a real thing.

18:05.752 --> 18:09.088
I'm telling you, she was just
doing it for the grade.

18:09.122 --> 18:11.324
And if it weren't for you,
I'd have a new fridge...

18:13.926 --> 18:15.628
What is it?

18:15.662 --> 18:17.930
**

18:17.964 --> 18:21.301
Hmm? Oh, you're into
my socks, girl?

18:21.334 --> 18:22.635
Thank you.

18:22.669 --> 18:24.137
Yeah, I would like to come back
to your house

18:24.171 --> 18:25.638
for some hot chocolate
and light kissing.

18:25.672 --> 18:27.006
[ Chuckles ]

18:27.039 --> 18:28.341
Do you feel a little bad
going ice skating

18:28.375 --> 18:29.742
after what we did to Evan?

18:29.776 --> 18:31.144
No.

18:31.178 --> 18:33.446
Ah, just who
I was looking for.

18:33.480 --> 18:36.316
You two are taking me to
the Teacher Supply Store.

18:36.349 --> 18:38.451
No way! We're just
about to go skating.

18:38.485 --> 18:41.921
If you refuse, I'll tell Mom
you took me to an R-rated movie.

18:41.954 --> 18:44.157
Are you blackmailing us?

18:44.191 --> 18:47.460
If putting a label on it helps
you swallow it, then sure.

18:47.494 --> 18:49.329
Sometimes you're the knife.
Sometimes you're the balloon.

18:49.362 --> 18:51.097
Now, chop chop,
you balloons.

18:51.130 --> 18:52.265
Mom will never
believe you.

18:52.299 --> 18:53.600
It's two against one,

18:53.633 --> 18:55.535
our word versus yours.

18:55.568 --> 18:57.170
Versus this ticket stub.

18:58.738 --> 19:00.573
Still think scrapbooking
is a joke?

19:03.243 --> 19:05.612
[ Knock on door, door opens ]

19:05.645 --> 19:07.680
Got a sec?

19:07.714 --> 19:10.550
[ Door closes ]

19:10.583 --> 19:12.485
I thought you hated the way
I painted your nails.

19:16.656 --> 19:19.058
I saw your
homework assignment.

19:19.091 --> 19:21.528
"My favorite hobby is...

19:21.561 --> 19:23.696
doing nails with Jessica."

19:31.037 --> 19:33.540
But we're not even
friendly with each other.

19:33.573 --> 19:35.375
You don't even look at me
when I do your nails.

19:50.223 --> 19:52.425
Always crying
during sports.

19:59.899 --> 20:02.068
I'm sorry I told you
I liked Bernard

20:02.101 --> 20:04.237
so I could use
your wheelchair.

20:04.271 --> 20:06.205
I hope we didn't
mess things up with him.

20:10.042 --> 20:11.544
[ Laughs ] I knew it!

20:11.578 --> 20:13.212
[ Sighs ]

20:17.617 --> 20:19.786
[ Both chuckle ]

20:23.089 --> 20:24.190
I know it's late,

20:24.223 --> 20:26.926
but do you want to
go shopping with me?

20:26.959 --> 20:29.529
All the good sales are over,
but who knows --

20:29.562 --> 20:31.731
we might see somebody
get trampled.

20:31.764 --> 20:33.966
I'd like that.

20:39.071 --> 20:40.039
Hey!

20:40.072 --> 20:42.275
I'm ready
for Black Friday!

20:42.309 --> 20:45.578
I just...I needed a little
hair of the dog.

20:45.612 --> 20:47.314
Here.

20:47.347 --> 20:48.948
Mm.

20:50.683 --> 20:53.820
Hey, so did I come over
yesterday?

20:53.853 --> 20:54.954
Were we all together?

20:54.987 --> 20:57.490
'Cause things
are a bit hazy.

20:57.524 --> 21:00.092
At some point,
I think I made nachos.

21:00.126 --> 21:03.730
And I also recall doing a load
of laundry in my underwear.

21:03.763 --> 21:06.599
And then I think I tried
to go for a run, and --

21:06.633 --> 21:07.600
Sure did.

21:07.634 --> 21:09.736
Ooh! Ooh!

21:09.769 --> 21:13.506
And then I woke up in bed under
the covers with my shoes on.

21:13.540 --> 21:15.342
And my hair was wet
for some reason.

21:15.375 --> 21:16.809
And Marvin's not
talking to me,

21:16.843 --> 21:18.911
which isn't a great sign.

21:18.945 --> 21:21.848
Yeah, so...

21:21.881 --> 21:24.317
did we hang out at all?

21:24.351 --> 21:26.453
[ Gulping ]
